<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFD0FFDD1687FADCFEB45FCC" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFD0FFDD1687FADCFEB45FCC" blockId="8.[151,1437,1333,1719]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1687FADCFE805CEC" bold="true" box="[199,338,1405,1431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD1717FADCFDE55CEC" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[343,567,1405,1431]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="funerea">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1717FADCFDE55CEC" box="[343,567,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sclerophrys funerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species known from west-central Africa, from 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFD0FFDD1229FADCFB665CEC" box="[1129,1204,1405,1431]" name="Gabon" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Gabon</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFD0FFDD1295FADCFAFE5CEC" box="[1237,1324,1405,1431]" name="Uganda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Uganda</collectingCountry>
and south to 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFD0FFDD16F3FA00FD8F5CC0" box="[179,605,1441,1467]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">the Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFD0FFDD14CFFA00FD335CC0" box="[655,737,1441,1467]" name="Angola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Angola</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFD0FFDD14AFFA00FC005CC0" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[751,978,1441,1467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1519FA03FC425CC0" box="[857,912,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFD0FFDD15A3FA00FB575CC0" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[995,1157,1441,1467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFD0FFDD12CFFA00FB1A5CC7" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[1167,1224,1441,1468]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">1906</bibRefCitation>
) cited several 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD1327FA00FF245CA4" authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1866" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Bufo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1327FA00FF245CA4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bufo funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with and without locality information data. Specimen MHNCUP/ANF 161 was labeled as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD134FFA67FA445CA4" baseAuthorityName="Reuss" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1295,1430,1477,1503]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD134FFA67FA445CA4" box="[1295,1430,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. regularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After reexamining the extant specimens previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD1522FA4BFC0D5F78" authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1866" box="[866,991,1513,1539]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Bufo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1522FA4BFC0D5F78" box="[866,991,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">B. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Ferreira, we found that most of them to correspond to either 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD17E1F9AFFD185F5C" authority="(Reuss, 1833)" baseAuthorityName="Reuss" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[417,714,1549,1576]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD17E1F9AFFDF75F5C" box="[417,549,1549,1576]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. regularis</emphasis>
(Reuss, 1833)
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD14B3F9AFFBC95F5C" authority="(Mertens, 1937)" baseAuthorityName="Mertens" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[755,1051,1549,1576]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD14B3F9AFFC8E5F5C" box="[755,860,1549,1576]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. pusilla</emphasis>
(Mertens, 1937)
</taxonomicName>
(see accounts below). The author mistakenly identified 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD17D0F993FDD65F30" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[400,516,1585,1612]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="funerea">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD17D0F993FDD65F30" box="[400,516,1585,1612]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. funerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD146EF993FD605F30" baseAuthorityName="Reuss" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[558,690,1585,1612]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD146EF993FD605F30" box="[558,690,1585,1612]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. regularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most likely due to the difficult and confusing characters used to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD1766F9F7FE455F14" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[294,407,1621,1648]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="funerea">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1766F9F7FE455F14" box="[294,407,1621,1648]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. funerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all remaining 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD1435F9F4FD285F14" authorityName="Tschudi" authorityYear="1838" box="[629,762,1621,1647]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD1435F9F4FD285F14" box="[629,762,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sclerophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This difficulty is still latent, as noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFD0FFDD1289F9F4FF365FE8" author="Channing, A. &amp; Rodel, M. - O." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref36281" refString="Channing, A. &amp; Rodel, M. - O. (2019) Field Guide to the Frogs &amp; Other Amphibians of Africa. Struik Nature, Cape Town, 408 pp." type="book" year="2019">Channing &amp; Rödel (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, who commented that 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFD0FFDD17A6F9DBFD8A5FE8" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[486,600,1657,1684]" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Sclerophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="funerea">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFD0FFDD17A6F9DBFD8A5FE8" box="[486,600,1657,1684]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. funerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by the absence of a tarsal fold that is replaced by a row of spiny tubercles.
</paragraph>
